  "prompt": "What iPhone apps are worth buying?",
  "response": "As of 2023, there are a number of iPhone apps that are often recommended for their utility, creativity, or entertainment value. Here's a selection across various categories that you might find worth purchasing:\n\n### Productivity:\n1. **Notion** - A versatile workspace app for note-taking, project management, and database creation.\n2. **OmniFocus** - A powerful task management app that helps users organize and prioritize tasks effectively.\n3. **Things 3** - A beautifully designed task manager for keeping track of projects and to-dos.\n\n### Creativity:\n1. **Procreate Pocket** - A professional-grade drawing app, ideal for artists who want to sketch on the go.\n2. **Affinity Photo** - A robust photo editing app that offers many features similar to Adobe Photoshop but at a lower price.\n3. **LumaFusion** - A highly regarded video editing app for creating high-quality videos directly on your iPhone.\n\n### Health & Fitness:\n1. **MyFitnessPal** - An app for tracking food intake and exercise, offering a large database of food items.\n2. **Headspace or Calm** - Apps dedicated to meditation and mindfulness that can help you manage stress and improve your mental health.\n3. **Streaks** - A habit tracking app designed to help you develop good habits and eliminate bad ones.\n\n### Finance:\n1. **YNAB (You Need A Budget)** - A personal budgeting tool that encourages users to take control of their finances.\n2. **Mint** - A comprehensive finance tracker that helps you manage your budget, investments, and bills.\n  \n### Travel:\n1. **CityMaps2Go** - An offline map and travel guide app that helps you navigate and discover new cities without needing internet access.\n2. **TripIt** - A travel organizer that keeps all your travel details in one place, making planning easier and more streamlined.\n\n### Entertainment:\n1. **Plex** - A media server app that lets you organize and stream your media collection across devices.\n2. **Infuse** - A powerful video player for watching your movies and shows with support for a wide range of formats.\n\n### Games:\n1. **Monument Valley** - A visually stunning puzzle game with unique gameplay and beautiful design.\n2. **Stardew Valley** - A popular farming simulation game that offers hours of gameplay and charm.\n\n### Utility:\n1. **1Password** - A robust password manager that helps users securely store and manage passwords.\n2. **TextExpander** - An app that helps you save time by creating shortcuts for frequently used text snippets.\n\n### Learning:\n1. **Duolingo** - A language learning app that\u2019s both fun and effective, with a wide range of languages available.\n2. **GoodNotes or Notability** - For digital note-taking, both offer great features for writing, drawing, and annotating.\n\n### Bonus:\n- **Apple's own apps** (like Pages, Numbers, and Keynote) are often bundled with purchases and provide great functionality for document creation and editing.\n\nWhen considering apps, it\u2019s also worth checking whether a subscription model is in place, as many apps offer more features through subscriptions. Always read reviews and see if the app meets your specific needs before purchasing!",
